1
00:00:04,504 --> 00:00:07,907
<i>Your son shoplifted from my store.</i>

2
00:00:07,974 --> 00:00:10,343
<i>We shouldn't let him manipulate us</i>
<i>any further.</i>

3
00:00:10,410 --> 00:00:11,878
<i>What is he demanding?</i>

4
00:00:11,945 --> 00:00:14,647
The victim is Hideyuki Sakuma,
40 years old.

5
00:00:14,714 --> 00:00:16,349
<i>The bullet extracted from the body</i>

6
00:00:16,416 --> 00:00:20,253
<i>was fired from the gun</i>
<i>that belonged to Keisuke's father.</i>

7
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,388
I did it.

8
00:00:23,456 --> 00:00:24,724
What about the gun?

9
00:00:24,791 --> 00:00:26,760
<i>I haven’t mentioned the time capsule.</i>

10
00:00:26,826 --> 00:00:28,028
<i>The gun will most likely</i>

11
00:00:28,094 --> 00:00:29,262
never appear ever again.

12
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:31,364
<i>The police asked me</i>
<i>when I was at the salon…</i>

13
00:00:31,431 --> 00:00:32,999
<i>When was the last time you used it?</i>

14
00:00:33,066 --> 00:00:35,301
Saturday, the 17th.

15
00:00:35,368 --> 00:00:36,936
<i>I have something I'd like to ask you.</i>

16
00:00:37,003 --> 00:00:38,938
Would you mind coming
to the police station?

17
00:00:39,005 --> 00:00:40,006
I decline.

18
00:00:40,073 --> 00:00:42,909
<i>Junichi, why did you become</i>
<i>a police officer?</i>

19
00:00:42,976 --> 00:00:44,711
<i>I shouldn't have become one.</i>

20
00:00:44,778 --> 00:00:46,146
<i>Thank you for coming.</i>

21
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:49,849
Let's all go find the gun.

22
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:51,818
<i>I asked you all to gather here</i>

23
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:56,156
<i>because I want to re-examine the incident</i>
<i>that happened 23 years ago.</i>

24
00:00:56,222 --> 00:00:57,791
When Officer Kiyohara was shot,

25
00:00:57,857 --> 00:01:01,027
<i>he dropped the gun he was holding.</i>

26
00:01:01,094 --> 00:01:04,597
The person who picked it up shot Oshima.

27
00:01:04,664 --> 00:01:06,599
<i>Who shot Oshima?</i>

28
00:01:07,167 --> 00:01:09,702
The first person to arrive
at this location.

29
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:13,740
<i>You shouldn't be</i>

30
00:01:15,375 --> 00:01:16,943
with someone like me!

31
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,621
I shot him.

32
00:01:42,802 --> 00:01:44,370
The person who killed Oshima…

33
00:01:46,539 --> 00:01:47,640
was me.

34
00:01:52,946 --> 00:01:54,514
When I got here,

35
00:01:55,748 --> 00:01:58,118
and saw the gunned down Officer Kiyohara,

36
00:01:58,184 --> 00:01:59,419
I spotted…

37
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,825
Oshima standing there.

38
00:02:09,095 --> 00:02:10,130
Our eyes met,

39
00:02:11,364 --> 00:02:12,432
<i>so I got scared</i>

40
00:02:15,068 --> 00:02:16,436
and tried to run away,

41
00:02:16,936 --> 00:02:18,705
but I tripped and fell…

42
00:02:22,108 --> 00:02:24,344
That’s when I felt Officer Kiyohara's gun.

43
00:02:25,178 --> 00:02:26,212
So I…

44
00:02:31,584 --> 00:02:32,418
<i>took it…</i>

45
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,091
I picked it up…

46
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:44,364
I picked it up

47
00:02:45,265 --> 00:02:47,867
and aimed it at Oshima.

48
00:02:53,306 --> 00:02:55,441
My mind went blank.

49
00:02:56,776 --> 00:02:57,610
And then?

50
00:02:58,411 --> 00:02:59,512
The gun?

51
00:03:01,714 --> 00:03:04,817
I left it here and returned to Naoto.

52
00:03:06,653 --> 00:03:09,622
Mr. Kiyohara and Ms. Iwamoto
were with Mr. Sakuma,

53
00:03:10,390 --> 00:03:12,158
so the four of you came here together?

54
00:03:14,894 --> 00:03:18,264
I am just as guilty as Junichi.

55
00:03:19,098 --> 00:03:20,400
What do you mean?

56
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:22,202
When Junichi first came here,

57
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:26,105
I had actually followed him here too.

58
00:03:29,042 --> 00:03:30,310
From around that area,

59
00:03:31,411 --> 00:03:34,347
I saw Junichi holding a gun.

60
00:03:36,449 --> 00:03:37,750
<i>Then I heard a gunshot…</i>

61
00:03:39,352 --> 00:03:42,388
<i>and I panicked</i>
<i>and ran away from the scene.</i>

62
00:03:44,157 --> 00:03:45,792
All this time, I kept quiet

63
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,629
about Junichi shooting Oshima.

64
00:03:51,097 --> 00:03:53,967
So I’m just as guilty as Junichi.

65
00:03:54,033 --> 00:03:55,235
So,

66
00:03:55,835 --> 00:03:58,838
when the four of you arrived here,

67
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:02,575
the gun was still lying near the body.

68
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:05,278
Is that correct?

69
00:04:08,147 --> 00:04:09,015
However,

70
00:04:09,515 --> 00:04:10,917
during the investigation conducted

71
00:04:10,984 --> 00:04:13,152
immediately after
the four of you were rescued,

72
00:04:13,219 --> 00:04:15,655
no gun was found.

73
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:20,860
What happened to the gun?

74
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:23,863
Are you

75
00:04:24,864 --> 00:04:28,301
suggesting that one of us took it?

76
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:29,969
Yes, that's a possibility.

77
00:04:30,036 --> 00:04:30,903
But

78
00:04:31,404 --> 00:04:34,941
my brother said he found the gun
in the forest.

79
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:53,593
I understand.

80
00:04:55,495 --> 00:04:56,496
Everyone,

81
00:04:57,063 --> 00:04:59,899
thank you all for your cooperation.

82
00:05:03,102 --> 00:05:06,639
Please don't tell anyone
about what we just discussed here.

83
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,611
Everything, including Detective Tobina's
shooting of Oshima,

84
00:05:12,278 --> 00:05:13,479
needs to stay

85
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:16,783
strictly confidential, just between us.

86
00:05:19,519 --> 00:05:20,787
Understood.

87
00:05:22,522 --> 00:05:23,523
Okay.

88
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:25,024
Okay.

89
00:05:58,691 --> 00:05:59,859
We'll be going now.

90
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:03,696
Thank you Mr. Kiyohara and Ms. Iwamoto.

91
00:06:16,676 --> 00:06:17,810
See you again.

92
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:56,716
Junichi shot Oshima in the back.

93
00:06:58,718 --> 00:07:02,355
If he shot Oshima
as he was trying to escape,

94
00:07:03,990 --> 00:07:06,259
it must have been to avenge my dad.

95
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:16,235
For 23 years, he kept it to himself,
without telling anyone,

96
00:07:17,970 --> 00:07:20,807
<i>and Naoto, who witnessed it,</i>
<i>also kept silent.</i>

97
00:07:24,744 --> 00:07:28,347
I thought I was the one suffering
the most, since my dad was killed,

98
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,752
but those guys were carrying
an even heavier burden.

99
00:07:36,722 --> 00:07:38,424
How were they able to cope with it?

100
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,898
<i>I can't imagine how Junichi must have felt</i>

101
00:07:46,833 --> 00:07:48,367
after shooting someone.

102
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:55,408
<i>When Naoto</i>

103
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:59,846
<i>suggested burying the gun</i>
<i>in the time capsule,</i>

104
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:04,150
<i>it wasn't just for me,</i>
<i>but for Junichi as well, huh?</i>

105
00:08:06,085 --> 00:08:06,919
<i>Yeah.</i>

106
00:08:09,522 --> 00:08:10,823
That's Naoto.

107
00:08:11,891 --> 00:08:12,992
Back then,

108
00:08:14,961 --> 00:08:18,464
what would have happened to Junichi
if I hadn't taken that gun with me?

109
00:08:20,933 --> 00:08:22,869
Would he have been caught?

110
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:36,382
Hey Makiko.

111
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:38,251
Yeah?

112
00:08:42,555 --> 00:08:43,456
I'll be going now.

113
00:09:02,108 --> 00:09:03,609
Detective Tobina.

114
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,848
- Yes?
- What should we do?

115
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:12,151
About reporting what I did?

116
00:09:12,218 --> 00:09:14,587
I mean lunch. What should we do for lunch?

117
00:09:25,031 --> 00:09:25,865
Um…

118
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:30,369
About reporting what happened
to the higher-ups…

119
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:32,538
Reporting what?

120
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:39,111
About how I shot Oshima 23 years ago.

121
00:09:39,178 --> 00:09:41,480
Remember what I said?

122
00:09:41,547 --> 00:09:44,083
What we discussed in the forest
stays strictly between us.

123
00:09:44,650 --> 00:09:46,919
You meant that for the other three, right?

124
00:09:46,986 --> 00:09:48,020
No.

125
00:09:48,087 --> 00:09:50,856
I have no intention of telling
any higher-ups in the police force.

126
00:09:51,557 --> 00:09:54,427
- Why?
- Because that case isn’t closed yet.

127
00:09:54,493 --> 00:09:57,263
Then all the more reason to report it.

128
00:09:57,897 --> 00:10:00,600
Just please keep quiet about this.

129
00:10:02,301 --> 00:10:03,536
Please.

130
00:10:13,045 --> 00:10:16,382
Even if I keep quiet, that doesn't mean
I can continue being a police officer.

131
00:10:16,449 --> 00:10:17,817
You're so irritating.

132
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:23,055
You’re quitting because the truth is out?

133
00:10:24,490 --> 00:10:26,792
Would you have continued
if you hadn't been found out?

134
00:10:28,127 --> 00:10:30,896
What made you become
a police officer in the first place?

135
00:10:31,764 --> 00:10:34,433
I can't believe you committed a crime
and became

136
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:36,402
a police officer.

137
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:38,471
It's ridiculous.

138
00:10:40,406 --> 00:10:41,841
What a mockery.

139
00:10:54,787 --> 00:10:56,589
That's why I think

140
00:10:58,524 --> 00:11:01,961
you became a police officer
because you committed a crime.

141
00:11:06,599 --> 00:11:07,600
Let's eat.

142
00:11:09,635 --> 00:11:12,104
This is not something we should talk about
while eating.

143
00:11:20,613 --> 00:11:21,781
Delicious.

144
00:11:30,990 --> 00:11:34,694
The gun that Naoto Sakuma
confessed to have used to kill

145
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:36,395
his older brother Hideyuki Sakuma,

146
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:39,765
the manager of Smile Sakuma,
has not yet been found.

147
00:11:39,832 --> 00:11:40,766
Sir.

148
00:11:41,267 --> 00:11:43,436
We are conducting a search
over a very wide area,

149
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:45,638
but we have not found the gun.

150
00:11:46,138 --> 00:11:48,040
Makiko Iwamoto told us

151
00:11:48,107 --> 00:11:50,409
she was at the hair salon
on the night of the incident,

152
00:11:50,476 --> 00:11:52,812
but it turns out that was a lie.

153
00:11:54,113 --> 00:11:56,415
There were witness reports of someone

154
00:11:56,482 --> 00:11:57,550
<i>at the hair salon that day,</i>

155
00:11:57,616 --> 00:12:00,720
<i>but that person was another hairdresser</i>
<i>and not Makiko Iwamoto.</i>

156
00:12:01,787 --> 00:12:04,724
Therefore, we asked her to
accompany us voluntarily, but she refused.

157
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:06,092
That's suspicious.

158
00:12:06,158 --> 00:12:08,027
The murder weapon hasn’t been found,

159
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:10,730
and there is no conclusive evidence
to indict Naoto Sakuma,

160
00:12:10,796 --> 00:12:12,765
but now Makiko Iwamoto's alibi
has fallen apart.

161
00:12:12,832 --> 00:12:13,566
PERSON OF INTEREST
MAKIKO IWAMOTO

162
00:12:13,632 --> 00:12:16,168
It'd be wise to consider the possibility
that Makiko Iwamoto

163
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,837
might know something about the gun.

164
00:12:17,903 --> 00:12:19,705
We can only have her come in voluntarily?

165
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:21,640
Yes, for now.

166
00:12:22,141 --> 00:12:23,442
What can you tell us

167
00:12:23,943 --> 00:12:26,011
about Naoto Sakuma’s excursion today?

168
00:12:27,046 --> 00:12:28,247
What do you mean?

169
00:12:29,014 --> 00:12:33,252
It seems that Detective Nara and Tobina
took Naoto Sakuma somewhere.

170
00:12:33,319 --> 00:12:34,220
What?

171
00:12:35,387 --> 00:12:37,556
Where did you go and what did you do?

172
00:12:40,826 --> 00:12:43,696
Unfortunately,
I wasn't able to get any results.

173
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:44,964
What did you do?

174
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:47,266
We went to the river where Naoto Sakuma

175
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:49,969
allegedly threw away the gun
and re-examined the location.

176
00:12:50,035 --> 00:12:52,104
We informed him about
Makiko Iwamoto's false alibi

177
00:12:52,171 --> 00:12:53,639
and tried to pressure him,

178
00:12:53,706 --> 00:12:55,541
but his statement remained unchanged.

179
00:12:57,243 --> 00:13:00,045
Is it becoming increasingly difficult
to indict Naoto Sakuma?

180
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:02,214
No, we can’t say that for certain.

181
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:05,584
However, headquarters
also wants a swift resolution.

182
00:13:05,651 --> 00:13:09,155
Please continue to do
a thorough search for the murder weapon

183
00:13:09,221 --> 00:13:12,992
and dedicate all your efforts to achieving
a quick resolution,

184
00:13:13,058 --> 00:13:14,460
since our reputation is on the line.

185
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,928
Yes sir.

186
00:13:15,995 --> 00:13:21,100
We must find out the truth no matter what.

187
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:26,372
INTERROGATION ROOM

188
00:13:29,175 --> 00:13:33,813
<i>We still haven't found the gun</i>
<i>you threw into the river.</i>

189
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:37,216
<i>I wonder where it went.</i>

190
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:40,386
<i>Maybe it made its way out to sea.</i>

191
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:44,790
Oh, that reminds me.

192
00:13:46,258 --> 00:13:49,895
Ms. Makiko Iwamoto was lying.

193
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:54,366
She said she was alone at the hair salon

194
00:13:54,433 --> 00:13:56,502
on the day of the incident,
but that wasn't true.

195
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:58,103
She wasn't there.

196
00:13:59,104 --> 00:14:00,573
We wanted to hear her side of the story,

197
00:14:00,639 --> 00:14:02,408
so we asked her to come in voluntarily,

198
00:14:02,474 --> 00:14:03,943
but she refused.

199
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:07,780
Why do you think she did that?

200
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:11,383
Because there's nothing in particular
to talk about?

201
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:15,788
Do you really believe that?

202
00:14:17,423 --> 00:14:21,060
I thought you might know the truth.

203
00:14:22,094 --> 00:14:23,495
The truth?

204
00:14:26,432 --> 00:14:28,567
After all,

205
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:31,871
you're good at keeping people's secrets,
aren't you?

206
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:42,514
Mr. Sakuma,

207
00:14:44,416 --> 00:14:47,653
did you really murder your brother?

208
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:51,557
Yes.

209
00:14:52,992 --> 00:14:54,393
I did it.

210
00:14:57,263 --> 00:14:58,264
<i>Ms. Nara,</i>

211
00:14:58,797 --> 00:15:01,767
you whispered something
during the interrogation,

212
00:15:02,268 --> 00:15:04,270
but was that to prevent it
from being recorded?

213
00:15:04,770 --> 00:15:06,305
Did I say something?

214
00:15:06,372 --> 00:15:07,206
What…

215
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:09,942
I didn’t say anything, right,
Detective Nagai?

216
00:15:14,813 --> 00:15:17,650
That's right.
I, Nagai, did not hear anything!

217
00:15:20,486 --> 00:15:21,487
Wow, finally.

218
00:15:29,828 --> 00:15:32,398
How was Naoto’s interrogation?

219
00:15:33,332 --> 00:15:35,034
Please ask Ms. Nara.

220
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,469
You were taken off the interrogation,

221
00:15:37,536 --> 00:15:39,571
but you're still her partner.

222
00:15:42,141 --> 00:15:44,143
You and I have known each other longer.

223
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:46,378
By only two months.

224
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:47,513
That’s more than enough.

225
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:54,820
Naoto Sakuma's testimony
remains unchanged.

226
00:15:54,887 --> 00:15:58,657
He says he committed the murder
and threw the gun into the river.

227
00:16:00,092 --> 00:16:01,026
Anything else?

228
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:06,231
I didn't quite understand what she meant,

229
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,335
but Ms. Nara told Naoto Sakuma,

230
00:16:09,401 --> 00:16:10,569
"After all,

231
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:13,272
you're good at keeping people's secrets,
aren't you?"

232
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:16,675
Ms. Nara was pursuing the angle

233
00:16:16,742 --> 00:16:19,478
that Naoto Sakuma is protecting
Makiko Iwamoto.

234
00:16:25,050 --> 00:16:26,051
What else?

235
00:16:26,852 --> 00:16:28,053
That’s it.

236
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,355
What else?

237
00:16:29,421 --> 00:16:30,889
Any little detail will help.

238
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:36,228
Oh, for the first time ever,
Ms. Nara said my name correctly.

239
00:16:39,365 --> 00:16:40,399
I don’t care about that.

240
00:16:40,899 --> 00:16:41,967
Right.

241
00:16:42,534 --> 00:16:44,636
Does my scalp feel tense?

242
00:16:44,703 --> 00:16:45,838
Yes, very.

243
00:16:45,904 --> 00:16:47,573
- Really?
- You must be tired.

244
00:16:47,639 --> 00:16:48,607
Really?

245
00:16:48,674 --> 00:16:51,076
That felt amazing.

246
00:16:51,143 --> 00:16:54,146
Your scalp was tense at first,
but it has loosened up now.

247
00:16:54,213 --> 00:16:56,815
Your face looks refreshed too.

248
00:16:56,882 --> 00:16:59,718
It's my first time
getting a scalp treatment.

249
00:16:59,785 --> 00:17:00,953
I'm so glad I came.

250
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,654
It'll help you sleep well tonight.

251
00:17:02,721 --> 00:17:04,456
- Is that right?
- Yeah.

252
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:05,457
I see.

253
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,493
Maybe I should recommend it
to Junichi too.

254
00:17:08,327 --> 00:17:10,095
He hasn't been sleeping well?

255
00:17:13,232 --> 00:17:15,534
Well, come anytime for a scalp treatment,

256
00:17:15,601 --> 00:17:18,370
a haircut, a perm, or hair coloring.

257
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,174
Thank you.

258
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:23,509
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

259
00:17:23,575 --> 00:17:25,477
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

260
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,722
- Hello.
- Welcome.

261
00:17:42,795 --> 00:17:43,996
Do you have more questions?

262
00:17:44,496 --> 00:17:46,432
Thank you for the other day.

263
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:51,270
Miho, can I ask you to step out
for a little bit?

264
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:54,006
Okay. I'll go shopping.

265
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:57,109
Excuse me.

266
00:18:03,182 --> 00:18:05,117
Sorry to bother you at work.

267
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:07,286
Yes, it's a bother.

268
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,223
I would like to talk with you,
Ms. Makiko Iwamoto.

269
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:16,128
I refused voluntary accompaniment.

270
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:17,996
We can talk here.

271
00:18:18,063 --> 00:18:19,631
I have a customer in 15 minutes.

272
00:18:19,698 --> 00:18:21,467
I only need five minutes.

273
00:18:22,935 --> 00:18:24,336
Could you please

274
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,738
keep what I'm about to tell you

275
00:18:27,673 --> 00:18:29,908
just between the two of us?

276
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,756
Wanna go somewhere?

277
00:18:45,324 --> 00:18:46,525
Go where?

278
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:49,461
I haven't been able
to take a break in a while so…

279
00:18:50,996 --> 00:18:52,030
We can do an overnight trip.

280
00:18:52,531 --> 00:18:56,335
Isn't there a place you've been
wanting to go, but haven't been able to?

281
00:18:57,903 --> 00:19:00,939
I did have a place,
but I don't want to go there right now.

282
00:19:01,707 --> 00:19:03,442
Then where do you want to go right now?

283
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,314
Okay.

284
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:13,952
If you won't tell me,
we'll end up going where I want to go.

285
00:19:14,019 --> 00:19:15,988
I never agreed to go in the first place.

286
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,357
Oh, come on.

287
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,496
Let's go somewhere.

288
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,870
Fine, I guess I can go with you.

289
00:19:32,704 --> 00:19:33,539
Really?

290
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,275
That's settled then.

291
00:19:36,341 --> 00:19:37,809
Think of where to go.

292
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:39,011
Stop that.

293
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:41,947
Stop it, I'm trying to do homework.

294
00:19:42,014 --> 00:19:43,682
Come on, just this once.

295
00:19:43,749 --> 00:19:44,983
Oh, jeez.

296
00:19:47,886 --> 00:19:48,720
You didn't get lost?

297
00:19:48,787 --> 00:19:50,722
Yeah. I had no problem.

298
00:19:50,789 --> 00:19:51,723
I'm glad.

299
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,527
It seems like you're still
as busy as ever.

300
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:56,562
Kind of.

301
00:20:02,301 --> 00:20:04,570
Do you live near here?

302
00:20:04,636 --> 00:20:05,604
Yeah.

303
00:20:05,671 --> 00:20:07,506
It's two stops from here by train.

304
00:20:07,573 --> 00:20:08,707
Is it an apartment?

305
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:09,775
Yeah.

306
00:20:13,579 --> 00:20:14,513
Oh,

307
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:17,616
I was just wondering
what kind of life you lead here.

308
00:20:17,683 --> 00:20:19,785
Since I've never asked before.

309
00:20:24,656 --> 00:20:26,291
You wanted to talk about something?

310
00:20:27,793 --> 00:20:28,627
Yeah.

311
00:20:31,830 --> 00:20:35,200
Can I let Masaki stay at your place?

312
00:20:39,037 --> 00:20:41,073
Did Masaki say that he wants to do that?

313
00:20:44,776 --> 00:20:48,146
He didn't say that exactly…

314
00:20:48,213 --> 00:20:50,215
Then why all of a sudden?

315
00:20:51,016 --> 00:20:52,618
Well because…

316
00:20:53,685 --> 00:20:55,053
He's your son.

317
00:21:00,626 --> 00:21:01,460
You can't do it?

318
00:21:03,996 --> 00:21:05,330
I can see it on your face.

319
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,301
Well, um…

320
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:13,872
Makiko,

321
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:17,843
there's something I've been wanting
to tell you…

322
00:21:20,646 --> 00:21:22,681
- The thing is…
- Oh.

323
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:27,252
Oh, hold on. What's the matter?

324
00:21:27,319 --> 00:21:28,453
What brings you here?

325
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:30,856
My exam ended early.

326
00:21:45,604 --> 00:21:47,572
This is my wife, Kotono.

327
00:21:49,041 --> 00:21:50,075
This is Makiko.

328
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,982
You remarried, huh?

329
00:21:58,350 --> 00:21:59,217
Yeah.

330
00:22:02,888 --> 00:22:04,122
I'm sorry.

331
00:22:04,189 --> 00:22:05,991
- I wasn't aware.
- Well…

332
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:08,493
I was just about to tell you about it…

333
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:10,495
When did you get married?

334
00:22:11,863 --> 00:22:13,532
A year ago.

335
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:16,768
Sorry.

336
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:18,904
I should've told you a lot earlier.

337
00:22:21,239 --> 00:22:22,708
I think I'll leave for now.

338
00:22:23,275 --> 00:22:24,109
- This is for the office.
- Wait.

339
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:25,610
- Wait.
- I'm done here, so…

340
00:22:25,677 --> 00:22:26,678
Wait a minute.

341
00:22:26,745 --> 00:22:28,980
It's okay,
I understand your situation now.

342
00:22:29,915 --> 00:22:32,451
I guess you can't help me
with my earlier request.

343
00:22:36,555 --> 00:22:38,156
When are you due?

344
00:22:39,991 --> 00:22:41,293
Next month.

345
00:22:41,793 --> 00:22:42,627
Wow.

346
00:22:43,295 --> 00:22:44,763
How exciting.

347
00:22:49,568 --> 00:22:51,603
Then I'll be going now.

348
00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:53,605
- Makiko.
- No worries.

349
00:22:54,106 --> 00:22:55,374
It's all right.

350
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:00,345
Please, take care.

351
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:02,748
Thank you.

352
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:32,878
MAKIKO IWAMOTO

353
00:23:43,588 --> 00:23:44,589
Come in.

354
00:23:49,361 --> 00:23:50,262
Where's Masaki?

355
00:23:50,996 --> 00:23:51,830
Is he asleep?

356
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:55,233
He's not here. He's at my parent's house.

357
00:23:57,502 --> 00:24:00,839
I don't want Masaki
to hear what I'm about to say.

358
00:24:07,679 --> 00:24:09,114
Are you hungry?

359
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,220
I think I'll eat after I get home.

360
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,422
Okay.

361
00:24:20,692 --> 00:24:22,194
I went to Tokyo today.

362
00:24:22,694 --> 00:24:23,562
I see.

363
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:26,798
I went to see Keisuke.

364
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:30,936
Keisuke has remarried.

365
00:24:33,538 --> 00:24:34,372
What?

366
00:24:35,607 --> 00:24:36,675
Keisuke?

367
00:24:37,676 --> 00:24:40,879
Are you serious? Wow.

368
00:24:40,946 --> 00:24:42,080
What the heck?

369
00:24:43,381 --> 00:24:44,216
What?

370
00:24:45,283 --> 00:24:46,952
Junichi, you knew already, didn't you?

371
00:24:47,018 --> 00:24:50,455
- Huh?
- You already knew. I'm sure of it.

372
00:24:53,191 --> 00:24:55,393
Even if I did, I had no right to tell you.

373
00:24:55,994 --> 00:24:57,262
I know that.

374
00:24:58,129 --> 00:25:00,966
But if that's how I was going to find out,

375
00:25:01,466 --> 00:25:03,168
I wish I had been told sooner.

376
00:25:04,536 --> 00:25:05,637
How did you find out?

377
00:25:06,204 --> 00:25:07,038
Well,

378
00:25:07,539 --> 00:25:09,841
before Keisuke could tell me about it,

379
00:25:10,342 --> 00:25:13,345
his wife happened to show up,
and that's how I found out.

380
00:25:14,479 --> 00:25:15,881
How does that even happen?

381
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:19,584
It's okay that you don't know.

382
00:25:31,696 --> 00:25:32,631
Are you okay?

383
00:25:38,236 --> 00:25:39,905
I was shocked.

384
00:25:42,474 --> 00:25:46,444
It never crossed my mind
that he'd get married again.

385
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:52,317
Also, when I thought about the fact

386
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:56,488
that Keisuke will be with the child
he is about to have,

387
00:25:57,856 --> 00:26:01,259
but not with Masaki,

388
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:04,462
it bothered me a little.

389
00:26:08,166 --> 00:26:09,434
Even though his remarriage

390
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:13,438
and having another child
are both such happy events.

391
00:26:21,379 --> 00:26:24,482
Was this what you wanted to talk about?

392
00:26:27,452 --> 00:26:28,753
It wasn't just this.

393
00:26:31,189 --> 00:26:32,657
It's about Naoto.

394
00:26:33,959 --> 00:26:34,893
How is he?

395
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:37,762
There's been no change.

396
00:26:39,497 --> 00:26:41,299
He says he did it.

397
00:26:46,071 --> 00:26:49,074
However, since the murder weapon
hasn't been found,

398
00:26:50,375 --> 00:26:52,677
and your alibi has been proven wrong,

399
00:26:55,113 --> 00:26:57,482
there isn't enough conclusive evidence
to file charges.

400
00:27:02,387 --> 00:27:05,290
I'm a suspect, aren't I?

401
00:27:05,991 --> 00:27:09,194
The entire investigation team
still considers Naoto to be the culprit.

402
00:27:10,495 --> 00:27:11,329
However…

403
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:15,667
Ms. Nara suspects you.

404
00:27:17,035 --> 00:27:18,036
What about you?

405
00:27:28,647 --> 00:27:29,547
First,

406
00:27:30,215 --> 00:27:33,151
I want to hear from you about your alibi
on the night of the incident.

407
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:37,722
Sorry.

408
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:40,225
Regarding that…

409
00:27:43,261 --> 00:27:45,196
Can you give me a little more time?

410
00:27:50,568 --> 00:27:51,536
Okay.

411
00:27:57,542 --> 00:27:59,110
Are you okay, Junichi?

412
00:28:06,051 --> 00:28:07,085
Me?

413
00:28:13,792 --> 00:28:15,360
What about you, Makiko?

414
00:28:19,931 --> 00:28:22,233
I'm sure you never expected me
to have shot someone.

415
00:28:26,538 --> 00:28:27,706
Junichi,

416
00:28:29,407 --> 00:28:31,876
you didn't tell anyone about that, right?

417
00:28:31,943 --> 00:28:32,777
Yeah.

418
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:38,583
I didn't know Naoto had seen me either.

419
00:28:41,753 --> 00:28:42,954
How did you cope with it?

420
00:28:43,455 --> 00:28:44,289
How did I cope?

421
00:28:44,789 --> 00:28:47,525
But… I mean…

422
00:28:47,592 --> 00:28:49,327
I was my usual self, right?

423
00:28:49,928 --> 00:28:51,396
Is that how

424
00:28:52,997 --> 00:28:56,434
you've been desperately trying
to keep yourself together every day?

425
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:01,940
Because otherwise,
just thinking about that day

426
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:05,744
will cause you to fall apart.

427
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:15,320
You may be right.

428
00:29:25,029 --> 00:29:26,331
How did you cope with it?

429
00:29:35,406 --> 00:29:36,241
I…

430
00:29:36,307 --> 00:29:38,743
I…

431
00:29:41,279 --> 00:29:42,113
Are you okay?

432
00:29:43,715 --> 00:29:44,849
I'm okay.

433
00:29:44,916 --> 00:29:46,017
I'm okay.

434
00:30:03,268 --> 00:30:07,105
I was desperately trying
to protect myself.

435
00:30:10,074 --> 00:30:11,643
I was only 12 years old,

436
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:16,247
so I couldn't be punished legally,

437
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:18,683
but

438
00:30:23,421 --> 00:30:25,223
I could never escape the fear.

439
00:30:28,927 --> 00:30:30,428
I was obviously…

440
00:30:33,164 --> 00:30:35,233
scared of people finding out

441
00:30:38,436 --> 00:30:39,637
who I really was.

442
00:30:44,576 --> 00:30:46,711
I don't think I deserve to be happy.

443
00:30:48,713 --> 00:30:50,849
Even when I live with someone,

444
00:30:52,050 --> 00:30:54,185
I make sure to maintain
a certain emotional distance.

445
00:30:58,122 --> 00:30:59,190
And…

446
00:31:02,126 --> 00:31:04,696
I tell myself that there's no point
in blaming myself anymore,

447
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:08,032
so I should try to do something useful

448
00:31:09,067 --> 00:31:10,235
for others.

449
00:31:11,502 --> 00:31:14,172
But I still feel like that's not enough
to forgive myself.

450
00:31:17,976 --> 00:31:20,979
When I have nightmares, it's difficult,
but there's also a sense of relief.

451
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:26,484
There were moments

452
00:31:28,620 --> 00:31:31,522
when I truly forgot about that incident.

453
00:31:33,391 --> 00:31:35,059
Even when I'm talking like this,

454
00:31:36,027 --> 00:31:38,029
it feels like I'm talking about
someone else.

455
00:31:39,197 --> 00:31:42,100
Sometimes I lose track of who I am,
and where I am.

456
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:45,770
I get confused.

457
00:31:49,574 --> 00:31:50,975
I get confused…

458
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:53,511
And that

459
00:31:58,983 --> 00:32:00,418
will never change.

460
00:32:11,062 --> 00:32:12,497
I can't undo the fact…

461
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:19,504
that I have committed a crime.

462
00:33:09,253 --> 00:33:10,288
Sorry about everything.

463
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:12,657
Not at all.

464
00:33:14,759 --> 00:33:15,660
I'll be going now.

465
00:33:17,095 --> 00:33:17,929
Okay.

466
00:33:29,774 --> 00:33:31,142
Junichi.

467
00:33:38,216 --> 00:33:39,117
Never mind.

468
00:33:40,718 --> 00:33:41,652
Bye.

469
00:33:43,688 --> 00:33:44,522
Bye.

470
00:33:56,267 --> 00:33:58,403
<i>Could you please keep</i>

471
00:33:59,003 --> 00:34:00,438
<i>what I'm about to tell you</i>

472
00:34:01,005 --> 00:34:03,307
just between the two of us?

473
00:34:04,308 --> 00:34:06,044
I can't promise you that.

474
00:34:06,811 --> 00:34:08,546
Not until I hear what it's about.

475
00:34:15,119 --> 00:34:19,123
In the forest, Detective Tobina
made a confession, right?

476
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:22,527
He said he shot Oshima 23 years ago.

477
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:27,265
That may be his misunderstanding.

478
00:34:28,499 --> 00:34:30,234
- Misunderstanding?
- Yes.

479
00:34:30,735 --> 00:34:33,071
I find it hard to believe

480
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:36,374
that the bullet fired by Detective Tobina
hit Oshima.

481
00:34:37,041 --> 00:34:37,875
What?

482
00:34:37,942 --> 00:34:40,978
Maybe he never fired the gun
in the first place.

483
00:34:43,114 --> 00:34:46,217
Is that even possible?

484
00:34:46,284 --> 00:34:47,151
Yes,

485
00:34:48,286 --> 00:34:50,421
if my deduction is correct, that is.

486
00:34:51,656 --> 00:34:52,523
Deduction?

487
00:34:53,024 --> 00:34:56,127
The key to solving this is that gun,

488
00:34:56,828 --> 00:34:58,863
but it has not yet been found
in the location

489
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:01,232
given to us by Mr. Naoto Sakuma.

490
00:35:03,101 --> 00:35:06,137
If only we could find the gun,

491
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:09,574
we could prove
Detective Tobina's misunderstanding.

492
00:35:10,842 --> 00:35:11,976
Why am I

493
00:35:12,977 --> 00:35:14,779
the only one you're sharing this with?

494
00:35:18,816 --> 00:35:20,685
I wonder why.

495
00:35:25,756 --> 00:35:28,159
<i>I don't think I deserve to be happy.</i>

496
00:35:30,361 --> 00:35:31,896
<i>I can't undo the fact…</i>

497
00:35:33,264 --> 00:35:35,366
that I have committed a crime.

498
00:36:02,927 --> 00:36:04,428
I'm back.

499
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:05,830
Welcome back.

500
00:36:09,534 --> 00:36:11,636
I'm famished.

501
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:16,407
I had a sudden craving for <i>nikujaga</i>.

502
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:17,675
You made it?

503
00:36:17,742 --> 00:36:19,944
Yeah. I even made the broth.

504
00:36:30,588 --> 00:36:31,522
Are you okay?

505
00:36:32,657 --> 00:36:33,624
Why?

506
00:36:35,393 --> 00:36:37,228
Were you crying?

507
00:36:39,096 --> 00:36:40,064
No.

508
00:36:41,599 --> 00:36:43,868
Oh, but I did yawn.

509
00:36:46,904 --> 00:36:48,039
That must be it.

510
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:49,907
I'm glad.

511
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,982
KEISUKE KIYOHARA

512
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:01,352
It's work.

513
00:37:01,419 --> 00:37:02,286
Okay.

514
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:07,692
Hello?

515
00:37:08,459 --> 00:37:09,794
<i>I'm getting a bad feeling.</i>

516
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:14,432
What's wrong?

517
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:17,134
I've been thinking about this a lot,

518
00:37:17,702 --> 00:37:19,971
but did Naoto really do it?

519
00:37:21,305 --> 00:37:23,741
I can't help but feel like Naoto
is covering for Makiko.

520
00:37:25,109 --> 00:37:27,478
I wanted to ask Makiko, but I couldn't.

521
00:37:28,412 --> 00:37:30,281
I don't think Makiko did it either,

522
00:37:30,348 --> 00:37:32,350
but I just have a bad feeling about this.

523
00:37:32,416 --> 00:37:35,820
<i>She asked if it would be okay for Masaki</i>
<i>to come and stay at my place.</i>

524
00:37:37,054 --> 00:37:37,888
Keisuke.

525
00:37:38,389 --> 00:37:39,223
<i>Yeah?</i>

526
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:45,730
Makiko's alibi has fallen apart.

527
00:37:47,231 --> 00:37:48,266
What do you mean?

528
00:37:48,332 --> 00:37:51,235
After meeting Makiko at the restaurant,
you went to your hotel,

529
00:37:51,302 --> 00:37:53,704
and Makiko supposedly
returned to the hair salon.

530
00:37:55,373 --> 00:37:57,475
But in reality,
she didn't go to the hair salon.

531
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:00,344
Then where was she?

532
00:38:01,779 --> 00:38:02,847
<i>We don't know.</i>

533
00:38:05,016 --> 00:38:06,550
<i>She's refusing to be questioned.</i>

534
00:38:08,886 --> 00:38:10,888
She might be willing to tell you.

535
00:38:11,722 --> 00:38:12,590
No.

536
00:38:14,425 --> 00:38:16,093
She told me she can't tell me yet.

537
00:38:16,160 --> 00:38:17,728
<i>What does that even mean?</i>

538
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:20,031
<i>What did she do?</i>

539
00:38:24,535 --> 00:38:25,703
What about you, Junichi?

540
00:38:27,872 --> 00:38:30,374
Do you think that Makiko did it?

541
00:39:00,037 --> 00:39:00,905
What is it?

542
00:39:05,543 --> 00:39:07,211
Did you really do it, Naoto?

543
00:39:08,179 --> 00:39:09,447
Yeah.

544
00:39:14,752 --> 00:39:18,022
When will I be indicted?

545
00:39:18,856 --> 00:39:21,125
No charges will be filed
unless we find the gun.

546
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:28,532
The police just need to find the gun

547
00:39:31,035 --> 00:39:32,837
at the location I tell you, right?

548
00:39:33,437 --> 00:39:34,338
Yeah.

549
00:39:36,140 --> 00:39:37,641
You can make that happen?

550
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:42,179
The gun's real location

551
00:39:43,748 --> 00:39:44,982
isn't the river.

552
00:39:47,551 --> 00:39:49,687
I hesitated to tell the truth
during the interrogation,

553
00:39:51,689 --> 00:39:53,858
but I didn't want to mention that place.

554
00:40:17,882 --> 00:40:19,316
<i>On the day of the wake,</i>

555
00:40:20,718 --> 00:40:23,687
after the four of us
dug up the time capsule,

556
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:27,391
I buried it back in there.

557
00:40:34,732 --> 00:40:35,866
<i>So that this time for sure,</i>

558
00:40:37,635 --> 00:40:39,637
it would be buried away forever.

559
00:41:32,690 --> 00:41:33,524
<i>What?</i>

560
00:41:34,024 --> 00:41:35,392
What do you mean it wasn't there?

561
00:41:35,459 --> 00:41:36,727
That's what I want to know.

562
00:41:40,764 --> 00:41:43,000
- It really wasn't there?
- Yeah.

563
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:47,104
The soil was soft, so it's possible
someone had dug it up before me.

564
00:41:49,974 --> 00:41:51,742
No way.

565
00:41:53,477 --> 00:41:55,312
That's not possible.

566
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:57,314
Because…

567
00:41:59,917 --> 00:42:02,319
The gun will never be found again.

568
00:42:13,264 --> 00:42:14,265
No.

569
00:42:15,199 --> 00:42:16,133
No…

570
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:18,335
Why?

571
00:42:20,971 --> 00:42:22,373
No!

572
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:25,609
Why, Maki?

573
00:42:28,846 --> 00:42:30,314
Hello.

574
00:42:30,381 --> 00:42:31,849
I'm so sorry,

575
00:42:31,916 --> 00:42:35,319
Manager called and said
that she won't be able to come in.

576
00:42:39,757 --> 00:42:42,693
I'm supposed to protect you, Maki.

577
00:42:44,461 --> 00:42:45,462
<i>I too…</i>

578
00:42:45,529 --> 00:42:47,731
have something I've been shouldering.

579
00:42:48,465 --> 00:42:50,067
<i>There's something I've decided</i>

580
00:42:50,968 --> 00:42:52,503
<i>to keep locked away in my heart</i>

581
00:42:54,004 --> 00:42:55,205
<i>for the rest of my life.</i>

582
00:42:56,540 --> 00:42:58,208
<i>But I just have a bad feeling about this.</i>

583
00:42:58,275 --> 00:43:00,744
<i>Did Naoto really do it?</i>

584
00:43:00,811 --> 00:43:03,180
<i>I can't help but feel like Naoto</i>
<i>is covering for Makiko.</i>

585
00:43:09,019 --> 00:43:11,155
<i>Do you think Makiko did it?</i>

586
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:15,292
<i>Sorry.</i>

587
00:43:15,826 --> 00:43:17,027
<i>Regarding that…</i>

588
00:43:17,895 --> 00:43:19,930
Can you give me a little more time?

589
00:43:19,997 --> 00:43:21,098
Junichi.

590
00:43:30,441 --> 00:43:32,543
Does Makiko have the gun?

591
00:43:39,216 --> 00:43:40,551
<i>How did you cope with it?</i>

592
00:43:41,585 --> 00:43:42,720
Is that how

593
00:43:44,321 --> 00:43:46,290
you've been desperately trying

594
00:43:46,357 --> 00:43:47,992
<i>to keep yourself together every day?</i>

595
00:43:51,128 --> 00:43:52,663
<i>Because just thinking about that day</i>

596
00:43:54,064 --> 00:43:55,966
<i>will cause you to fall apart.</i>

597
00:44:05,309 --> 00:44:06,343
Did Makiko

598
00:44:08,846 --> 00:44:11,415
shoot Hideyuki Sakuma with that gun?

599
00:44:12,750 --> 00:44:14,551
FINALLY ENTERING THE FINAL CHAPTER

600
00:44:14,618 --> 00:44:16,353
<i>Makiko is gone.</i>
<i>I can't get in touch with her.</i>

601
00:44:16,420 --> 00:44:18,155
<i>There's something</i>
<i>I've been keeping from you.</i>

602
00:44:18,222 --> 00:44:19,823
<i>If anyone dug it up, it's Makiko.</i>

603
00:44:19,890 --> 00:44:22,292
<i>I'm the one who has to protect Maki.</i>

604
00:44:22,359 --> 00:44:25,262
<i>I'm sorry I haven't been able to</i>
<i>tell you the truth.</i>

605
00:44:25,329 --> 00:44:25,996
WHO CAN THE TRUTH SAVE?

606
00:44:26,063 --> 00:44:27,698
Please help Makiko.

607
00:44:27,765 --> 00:44:28,666
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
